* Updated Az.Batch to use 'Microsoft.Azure.Batch' SDK version 15.3.0_x000D__x000A_ - Add ability to assign user-assigned managed identities to 'PSCloudPool'. These identities will be made available on each node in the pool, and can be used to access various resources._x000D__x000A_ - Added 'IdentityReference' property to the following models to support accessing resources via managed identity:_x000D__x000A_ - 'PSAzureBlobFileSystemConfiguration'_x000D__x000A_ - 'PSOutputFileBlobContainerDestination'_x000D__x000A_ - 'PSContainerRegistry'_x000D__x000A_ - 'PSResourceFile'_x000D__x000A_ - 'PSUploadBatchServiceLogsConfiguration'_x000D__x000A_ - Added new 'extensions' property to 'PSVirtualMachineConfiguration' on 'PSCloudPool' to specify virtual machine extensions for nodes_x000D__x000A_ - Added the ability to specify availability zones using a new property 'NodePlacementConfiguration' on 'VirtualMachineConfiguration'_x000D__x000A_ - Added new 'OSDisk' property to 'VirtualMachineConfiguration', which contains settings for the operating system disk of the Virtual Machine._x000D__x000A_ - The 'Placement' property on 'PSDiffDiskSettings' specifies the ephemeral disk placement for operating system disks for all VMs in the pool. Setting it to 'CacheDisk' will store the ephemeral OS disk on the VM cache._x000D__x000A_ - Added 'MaxParallelTasks' property on 'PSCloudJob' to control the maximum allowed tasks per job (defaults to -1, meaning unlimited)._x000D__x000A_ - Added 'VirtualMachineInfo' property on 'PSComputeNode' which contains information about the current state of the virtual machine, including the exact version of the marketplace image the VM is using._x000D__x000A_ - Added 'RecurrenceInterval' property to 'PSSchedule' to control the interval between the start times of two successive job under a job schedule._x000D__x000A_ - Added a new 'Get-AzBatchComputeNodeExtension' command, which gets a specific extension by name, or a list of all extensions, for a given compute node._x000D__x000A_* Updated Az.Batch'Microsoft.Azure.Management.Batch' SDK version 14.0.0._x000D__x000A_ - Added a new 'Get-AzBatchSupportedVirtualMachineSku' command, which gets the list of Batch-supported Virtual Machine VM sizes available at a given location._x000D__x000A_ - Added a new 'Get-AzBatchTaskSlotCount' command, which gets the number of task slots required by a given job._x000D__x000A_ - 'MaxTasksPerComputeNode' has been renamed to 'TaskSlotsPerNode', to match a change in functionality._x000D__x000A_ - 'MaxTasksPerComputeNode' will remain as an alias but will be removed in a coming update.
